The book is made up of parchment and paper in equal proportione, the outer and inner leaves of each quire being of parchment. Sixteen leaves of paper have been inserted at the beginning and twelve at the end of the book, easily distinguished by the water-mark and chain-lines from the paper originally used in the book itsels. Most os these are blank, but some have writing, mostly in sixteenth-century hands.
